Definitions
----------------------------------------

 1. "Source"/"Source code"/"Source files" shall mean all files
    which contain source code that, by a compiling process,
    generate binary files. Source files have, but not
    necessarily, a *.typ or a *.svg extension.
 2. "Binary" shall mean all files which are product of a compilation of the
    source files. Binary files have, but not necessarily, a *.pdf extension.
 3. "Binary information" shall mean all text and/or images contained inside the
    binary files that are human-readable, not necessarily in a specific
    language such as English.


